over-prep for the M&M?

528
00:28:07,227 --> 00:28:08,353
Yes.

529
00:28:09,271 --> 00:28:11,606
Then say so, don't be a child.

530
00:28:13,817 --> 00:28:15,526
Is it on his penis?

531
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:18,446
The kid's rash?

532
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:19,906
Yeah, why?

533
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:23,368
Means it's most likely affecting
the small blood vessels.

534
00:28:23,452 --> 00:28:27,163
That's why we didn't see any
inflammation on the biopsies.

535
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:31,667
It's not polyarteritis,
it's Degos disease.

536
00:28:38,926 --> 00:28:40,385
I'll do it.

537
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:56,776
Your son has Degos disease.

538
00:28:57,694 --> 00:29:00,071
It causes micro-blood
vessels in the brain,

539
00:29:00,155 --> 00:29:03,950
skin, and GI tract to
break down, clot off.

540
00:29:06,161 --> 00:29:11,582
It sometimes manifests early on
with atrophic papules on the penis.

541
00:29:11,667 --> 00:29:16,129
In your son's case, we don't know
why, but they came much later.

542
00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:20,049
What's the treatment?

543
00:29:22,386 --> 00:29:24,011
There isn't one.

544
00:29:24,513 --> 00:29:26,013
It's incurable.

545
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:33,938
You're wrong.

546
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:38,109
You've already been
wrong a bunch of times.

547
00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:41,821
We rechecked the biopsies.
It's definitely Degos.

548
00:29:46,368 --> 00:29:49,704
I'm sorry. I wish there was
something we could do.

549
00:29:56,378 --> 00:29:57,712
How long?

550
00:29:58,964 --> 00:30:00,631
Not much longer.

551
00:30:02,885 --> 00:30:04,719
What does that mean?

552
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,555
A day at the most.

553
00:30:51,892 --> 00:30:53,643
All right. Great.

554
00:30:53,727 --> 00:30:55,353
We need to talk.

555
00:30:55,437 --> 00:30:57,271
Unless it's life or death,
it's gonna have to wait.

556
00:30:57,356 --> 00:30:59,106
It's about Dibala.

557
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:01,025
Let me rephrase,
unless it's a current...

558
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:03,778
Foreman can't present
the case at the M&M.

559
00:31:04,571 --> 00:31:08,199
I know you guys are busy, but he's just
gonna have to suck it up and make the time.

560
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:09,242
It's not the time.

561
00:31:09,326 --> 00:31:10,826
Then what is it?

562
00:31:11,453 --> 00:31:13,704
The anticentromere
antibodies test,

563
00:31:13,789 --> 00:31:15,665
the test that caused us
to change the treatment

564
00:31:15,749 --> 00:31:20,962
from blastomycosis
to scleroderma, it wasn't...

565
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:23,297
It wasn't what?

566
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:27,218
Dr. Cuddy, they need you
in the Pediatric ICU.

567
00:31:27,302 --> 00:31:28,803
Who's they? I don't know,

568
00:31:28,929 --> 00:31:31,138
but I think they're lawyers.

569
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:36,686
If you guys screwed something
up, just come clean.

570
00:31:37,771 --> 00:31:39,939
It's not gonna be that bad.

571
00:31:42,734 --> 00:31:45,278
With all due respect, you don't
know what's at stake here.

572
00:31:45,362 --> 00:31:47,196
What's going on?
You need to stop him.

573
00:31:47,281 --> 00:31:48,402
He's about to ruin his life.

574
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:49,865
Like you give a damn
about my life.

575
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:51,117
Roy, he's right.

576
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:54,245
You're borrowing money to buy options
that are already out of the money.

577
00:31:54,329 --> 00:31:56,163
Even you won't be able
to cover the losses.

578
00:31:56,248 --> 00:31:59,625
Your house, cars, bank accounts,
you'll lose everything.

579
00:31:59,710 --> 00:32:01,377
That's the point.

580
00:32:03,005 --> 00:32:06,924
The billionaire thinks that the gods
will treat him better if he's broke.

581
00:32:07,009 --> 00:32:08,259
I suggested he give it to me...

582
00:32:08,343 --> 00:32:10,636
There has got to be
some sort of balance.

583
00:32:10,721 --> 00:32:13,889
You can't have all the good fortune
in just one area of your life.

584
00:32:13,974 --> 00:32:16,851
That's not how the world's
supposed to work.

585
00:32:16,935 --> 00:32:18,394
Who said the world
was supposed to work?

586
00:32:18,478 --> 00:32:19,998
Don't just
wipe everything out.

587
00:32:20,022 --> 00:32:21,981
Put your assets in a trust,

588
00:32:22,065 --> 00:32:23,608
give it to a charity...
I can't get anything back.

589
00:32:23,692 --> 00:32:25,901
He's insane. He's irrational,

590
00:32:25,986 --> 00:32:29,113
so are most people. Unfortunately,
it doesn't make them insane.

591
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:32,950
If he signs that paper, he's not
only gonna destroy his own life,

592
00:32:33,035 --> 00:32:36,412
but the lives of thousands of people who
rely on this company to make a living.

593
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:38,256
If he is insane,
we will sue this hospital...

594
00:32:38,332 --> 00:32:40,207
Mr. Randall,

595
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:45,630
I know you're upset, but you shouldn't
make a decision like this right now.

596
00:32:45,714 --> 00:32:47,381
Give it some time.

597
00:32:48,634 --> 00:32:50,426
My son doesn't have any time.

598
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:53,888
Your son's dying from an incurable
disease, not bad karma.

599
00:32:53,972 --> 00:32:56,891
No. He's not dying.

600
00:32:58,060 --> 00:33:00,019
It's not gonna happen.
I'm not gonna let it.

601
00:33:00,103 --> 00:33:01,228
Roy.

602
00:33:02,314 --> 00:33:03,648
Please.

603
00:33:07,402 --> 00:33:10,696
I'm sorry. I can't let him die.

604
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:12,823
People don't get
what they deserve.

605
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:17,495
They just get what they get, and there's
nothing any of us can do about it.

606
00:33:26,088 --> 00:33:30,049
Deliver it, or I'll make sure you
end up the ones with nothing.

607
00:33:41,353 --> 00:33:43,688
Call a code. He's flat-lining.

608
00:34:01,081 --> 00:34:02,331
Thanks.

609
00:34:02,958 --> 00:34:05,000
You're welcome. For what?

610
00:34:05,335 --> 00:34:08,921
For thinking I was worth
breaking the law to keep around.

611
00:34:09,297 --> 00:34:10,715
That's just the way I am.

612
00:34:10,799 --> 00:34:12,550
But still don't know
what you're talking about.

613
00:34:12,634 --> 00:34:17,346
Cuddy had IT trace all the IP addresses
who've logged into my e-mail account.

614
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:20,766
There were two. Mine and yours.

615
00:34:22,519 --> 00:34:24,854
Obviously House decided he needs
you more than he's willing to...

616
00:34:24,938 --> 00:34:26,480
I already asked House.

617
00:34:27,482 --> 00:34:28,774
And he'd certainly never lie.

618
00:34:28,859 --> 00:34:32,278
No, he'd lie.
Except he wants me gone.

619
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:36,240
And he'd do a lot better job
of lying than you just did.

620
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:38,784
Really? It was that bad?

621
00:34:38,869 --> 00:34:40,536
No, actually.

622
00:34:41,163 --> 00:34:47,626
But it doesn't matter any more. Why?
Because of House or Foreman?

623
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:52,631
You're good for both of them, but
Foreman's not my best friend.

624
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:54,508
House will be fine.

625
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:56,135
Maybe.

626
00:34:56,219 --> 00:34:58,512
But with you on the
team, he'd be better.

627
00:34:58,597 --> 00:35:03,267
He needs someone
who doesn't need him.

628
00:35:03,351 --> 00:35:07,897
You're the only one he's never really been
able to suck into his crazy House vortex.

629
00:35:07,981 --> 00:35:10,816
Keeps him grounded,
his ego in check.

630
00:35:10,901 --> 00:35:12,359
Why didn't you just come to me?

631
00:35:14,362 --> 00:35:20,618
I figured you'd only stay if House asked.
And I knew he would, eventually.

632
00:35:24,247 --> 00:35:25,706
Bye, Wilson.

633
00:35:29,002 --> 00:35:30,836
This is a great job.

634
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:34,632
Maybe even better, now that
House is at least trying

635
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:37,176
to have real relationships
with people.

636
00:35:37,928 --> 00:35:39,470
I said trying.

637
00:35:40,138 --> 00:35:41,180
It doesn't matter.

638
00:35:41,264 --> 00:35:43,557
The job you love
doesn't matter?

639
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:47,770
Don't throw it all away just
because of a bad breakup.

640
00:35:50,899 --> 00:35:52,274
Bye, Wilson.

641
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:04,703
I just confessed.

642
00:36:05,330 --> 00:36:08,749
I told Thirteen I was the one
who canceled the plane ticket.

643
00:36:08,834 --> 00:36:09,834
Why?

644
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:12,169
You mean why did I confess,
or why did I do it?

645
00:36:12,254 --> 00:36:15,506
